sub_title: Public Accountant with degree on Argentina, looking to have another one in Uruguay.
summary:
Achievements and Interests: 
•	One of my proudest achievements is graduating from Rosario University. I moved to Uruguay in order to share my life with my partner two years prior to my graduation, so I studied on my own without attending classes nor having access to books. Furthermore, I travelled 20 hours for each test and as a result I believe that I have become a more resilient and hard-working person.
•	Another important experience was working for the Rudeli Company. When I arrived there, none of the employees had any background related to accountancy or administrative tasks, so the system they had was in total disorder and nothing close to the accounting laws standards. In order to solve the problem, I had to take a specific course from the system provider and learn how to master it. I had to remove all the data that the company stored, restart the system in an appropriate way -considering the law- and re-enter the data. Finally, I took on the responsibility to teach all the employees how to use the new system.
•	I am curious about different cultures and open to travel whenever is required.
